<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Titles, names, short phrases, and slogans; familiar symbols or designs; mere variations of typographic ornamentation, lettering, or coloring; mere listings of ingredients or contents<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hence, unless you can build a convincing case that the name &quot;Arikel&quot; would be an exception to this rule, again you have no game.  Zero.  Nada.  Zip.<br>
<br>
Here's a link, in case you don't believe me: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.loc.gov/copyright/circs/circ1.html#wnp">www.loc.gov/copyright/cir...1.html#wnp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
